records.addlTxt:
Defendant Michael Brian Kohl in court with attorney Terese M. Dick.  Defendant Michael Brian Kohl in custody.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 9 MONTHS in the House of Correction CONSECUTIVE to 15CM003297; credit for 69 days time served; STRAIGHT TIME.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 2 YEARS.
Conditions:  
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Participate in vocational training;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Court ordered costs and surcharges waived due to the defendant's inability to pay.  Court ordered restitution set at $0.00.  Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
